━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
PERMITTED (FREE) USES
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

You may use, copy, modify, and run this software at no cost if ALL of the
following are true:

  1. You are a defense contractor, subcontractor, or small business running
     the tool SOLELY for your own internal CMMC / NIST 800-171 readiness
     assessment — i.e., assessing systems you own or operate.

  2. You do NOT provide the output, reports, or any derivative work to an
     external paying client as part of a commercial cybersecurity, consulting,
     or managed-service engagement.

  3. You retain all copyright notices, the ASCII banner, the HTML footer
     attribution, and the SBOM tool-vendor metadata ("MSTechAlpine") in every
     artifact this software produces.

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
PROHIBITED (COMMERCIAL) USES — REQUIRES PAID LICENSE
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

The following uses ARE commercial and require a separate written license from
MSTechAlpine Ventures LLC:

  a. Using this tool to generate CMMC evidence, reports, or SBOMs that are
     delivered to a third-party (a client) as part of a paid or in-kind
     cybersecurity consulting, C3PAO pre-assessment, audit readiness, or
     managed-security-services engagement.

  b. Bundling, repackaging, white-labeling, or reselling this software or its
     output as part of a commercial product offering.

  c. Running this tool on behalf of another company, even without charge, as
     part of a business relationship that provides security services.

  d. Incorporating this code into a Software-as-a-Service (SaaS) platform or
     any platform that serves multiple external organizations.

━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
ATTRIBUTION REQUIREMENT (NON-NEGOTIABLE)
━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━

Any permitted use — including internal use — must preserve the following in
all generated artifacts:

  • The "MSTechAlpine Fleet Commander" credit in all HTML reports.
  • The "MSTechAlpine" vendor field in all CycloneDX / SPDX SBOM outputs.
  • The copyright notice in all source files.

Removing, altering, or obfuscating attribution — for any reason, including
"white-labeling" for a client — is a breach of this license and voids the
validity of the technical evidence produced.

